[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Strengths
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Exceptional problem framing.** The opening scenario (care manager with 200 patients, 8 call slots) immediately grounds the technical content in clinical reality. This is the best problem statement in Chapter 7.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Honest complexity acknowledgment.** The recipe correctly positions this as research/pilot, doesn't oversell causal inference capabilities, and recommends starting with the hybrid approach.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Self-fulfilling prophecy discussion.** Calling out how successful intervention erodes training signal is a sophisticated insight that most healthcare ML content ignores.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Intervention fatigue modeling.** Including dampening factors for recent contact and declined outreach shows real-world operational awareness.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **Architecture matches the problem.** The split between batch (model training, daily features) and real-time (event-driven scoring) paths is appropriate for the latency requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - **The "Honest Take" section is genuinely honest.** It doesn't hedge with corporate language; it tells the reader what will actually happen when they try to build this.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
